commit 17262f7e37a0fc7fe6f53fc3b19c9b5276e051f6
Author: Johannes Weiner <hannes@cmpxchg.org>

mm: switch deferred split shrinker to list_lru

This commit converts the deferred split queue from a custom per-node and
per-cgroup queue to use list_lru. It also adds on-demand allocation of
the list_lru for splittable pages during anonymous faults, swapin faults,
and khugepaged collapse.

> The list_lru per-memcg heads are instantiated on demand when the first
> object of interest is allocated for a cgroup, by calling
> folio_memcg_list_lru_alloc(). Add calls to where splittable pages are
> created: anon faults, swapin faults, khugepaged collapse.

Does this miss device memory migration paths?

When migrating a THP from device private memory back to system memory, the
migration code allocates a new THP and charges it to the memcg but does not
seem to call folio_memcg_list_lru_alloc(). 

If this THP is later partially unmapped, could deferred_split_folio()
encounter a NULL list_lru, trigger a kernel warning for a non-dying cgroup,
and break memcg isolation by falling back to the parent memcg?

> diff --git a/mm/huge_memory.c b/mm/huge_memory.c
> --- a/mm/huge_memory.c
> +++ b/mm/huge_memory.c

