Does the goto fallback path in these allocation loops miss the statistics
updates?

When the list_lru allocation fails, it bypasses the next label where
count_mthp_stat() records the fallback, leaving these failed huge page
allocations unaccounted for in the system's fallback statistics. 

In vma_alloc_anon_folio_pmd(), these stats appear to be correctly updated on
list_lru allocation failure. Should these paths also record the fallback
statistics before bailing out?

